          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":15,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Let your body recover and set the foundation for the week ahead.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run 5 km at 7:00–8:00 /km. Focus on conversational pace — if you can't speak in sentences, slow down. This is aerobic base-building, not a test.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Recovery is where adaptation happens — this day is doing real work.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Three running days per week is your structure — trust the spacing.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run 5 km at 7:00–8:00 /km. Notice how your body feels compared to Monday. Consistency over intensity at this stage.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day ahead of your long run tomorrow. Light movement like walking is fine if it feels good.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run 5 km at 7:30–8:00 /km — slightly easier than your midweek runs. The goal is time on feet, not speed. Enjoy the process.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Sarah! This opening week matches your current training volume exactly — 15 km across 3 runs — so there's no shock to the system, just a clear structure to build from. All three runs are easy effort, which is exactly right for someone six months in with a solid base to grow. The physiological goal this phase is building aerobic capacity and connective tissue resilience. Your easy pace of 7:00–8:00 /km is your best friend right now — it drives cardiovascular adaptation while keeping injury risk low. How does this layout feel as a starting point?\"}"
        }
      ]
